supervisions.notes:
Probation Review Hearing scheduled for 03/20/2015 @ 8:30am, Br-17

Court approved participation in Dosage Probation Pilot Program and early termination of probation, if defendant successfully completes program and all other conditions of probation.

miscConds.notes: Provide DNA sample, if not already done. Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including DNA surcharge, during the course of probation to the probation Agent. Any remaining balance due at the end of probation will become immediately due or civil judgment to be entered. Cash bail applied.

No possession of any firearms or weapons, firearm ammunition, firearm holster or case; Defendant may not be by any residence where any firearm, ammunition, holster or case is kept. Purusant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions: Firearm possession and Voting.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION, IF REVOKED:
- Maintain absolute sobriety, no alcohol.
- No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed.
- Participate in Alcohol and and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment including drug and alcohol testing.
- Defendant must attend at least one Alcohol and Drug Assessment treatment or sobriety support group per week.
- No possession of any drug paraphernalia for personal use, manufacturing, delivering, or distributing.
- Complete GED program.
- Obtain/maintain full time work and/or school.
- Court ordered defendant to comply with paying DOC's supervision fees.
- Court ordered defendant to comply with all Child Support Court orders.
- No contact with any gang member or any associate of a gang.

If revoked, Court notified defendant: Court advises the defendant that under Wisconsin Statute 302.113 the amount acutally served may be extended, and that the defendant could serve the entire bifurcated sentence in prison. The defendant will be subject to certain conditions while on release to extended supervision, and a violation of any of those conditions may result in the defendant being returned to prison.

timeConds.notes: STRAIGHT TIME; with no release privileges, and Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring

Defendant William Edward Jones in court with attorney Ann T. Bowe.  Karl P. Hayes appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 5 YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence; with credit for 6 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.  
Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program. 
Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 3 YEARS with the following conditions:
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
- Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including
  the DNA surcharge, during the course of probation to the probation agent. 
  Any remaining balance due at the end of probation will become immediately due
  or civil judgment to be entered. 
- Maintain Absolute Sobriety, no alcohol.
- No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid 
  prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed.
- Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment
  and successfully complete recommended treatment
  including drug and alcohol testing. 
- Defendant must attend at least one Alcohol and Drug Assessment
  treatment or sobriety support group per week. 
- No possession of any drug paraphernalia for personal use, manufacturing, delivering, or distributing.
- No possession of any firearms or weapons, firearm ammunition, firearm holster or case; Defendant may not be any residence where any firearm, ammunition, holster or case is kept. 
- Complete GED program. 
- Obtain/Maintain full time work and/or school.
- Court ordered Defendant to comply with paying Department of Correction Supervision fees. 
- Court ordered Defendant to comply with all child support court orders. 
- Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not already done. 
- No contact with any gang member or any associate of a gang. 
-Court imposes and stays 6 months of condition time, straight time  with no release privileges, and Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring. 

-Court approved participation in Dosage Probation Pilot Program and early termination of probation if defendant successfully completes program and all other conditions of probation.
 
Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.
If revoked Court notified Defendant: Court advises the Defendant that under Wisconsin Statute 302.113 the amount actually served may be extended, and that the Defendant could serve the entire bifurcated sentence in prison. The Defendant will be subject to certain conditions while on release to extended supervision, and a violation of any of those conditions may result in the Defendant being returned to prison. 
 
Case is scheduled for Probation Review Hearing 3-20-2015 at 8:30 a.m., Br. 17.
